	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Using this spell, along with Vampiric Embrace (or a few lifespikes if that's your cup-o-tea), with my pet at my side.. I've gone into battle with about 4 things at once, and kept my HP at near full, along with Mana at a good amount (initially starting battle off with a few DOTs while my pet distracts, then I'd charge in).  So, basically, I could practice melee, practice my spells without losing much at all, and my skeleton friend in there with a rusty 2h sword.. At level 8.. actually, many levels above this.. It's a great way to solo and gain levels without losing too much downtime.  I went from 9-11 in about 2 hours without difficulty.  Not only that, but it helps to keep all your skills, used, at max for each level.
				</font>
			</td>

